@NODE What_is_it? "What is it?"

M-TagFS is a powerfull file List/Tag program for DLG BB/OS.  It offers much
to the user which currently is not available in the one package.

Some features are:

       o Conforms to users ANSI color settings.
       o Full-screen layout.
       o User can scroll in both directions.
       o Easy point and tag tagging.
       o Multi-file numeric tagging.
       o Correctly handles global file paths.
       o Shows files which are already tagged.
       o Can toggle the display of descriptions.
       o Shows file info, including approximate download time.
       o Keeps user informed of their current batch size.
       o Views archives/text files.
       o 6 different sort methods.
       o Description length fits users screen width.
       o Sysop editable on-line help file.  Change it to your liking/
         language. Can also use DLG %-switches!
       o Multiple help files for BBS's with multi-lingual users.
       o Fast/Slow cursor support.
       o Internal area changing with FULL security check.
       o Supports private file area.
       o Handles SIG's. Shows only files in current SIG if the sysop so
         desires.
       o Handles broadcasted messages.
       o Shows long descriptions intelligently. If the user already has the
         full description, a simple message is sent to them.
       o Correctly handles local mono (IE no RED!)
       o Searches for files. Same search keyword works even after changing
         areas.
       o Global file searching achieved with external program (included).
       o User can jump to next available area with a key press, both forward
         and reverse directions.
       o Updates 'T:<port>.user' to reflect actions taken in M-TagFS.
       o Can revert to tag status at beginning of current entry.
       o Correctly handles CD-ROM areas that have been uploaded as normal
         areas.
       o Sysop defineable external batch editing ability.
       o Displays 'EnterArea.TXT' if one exists when user enters the area.
       o Tells DLG there is a user in current area, and doesn't allow a user
         in if the area is locked.
       o Customiseable header.

@ENDNODE

@NODE config "M-TagFS config file"

A config file is @{b}required@{bu} with M-TagFS. The included config file can be
used as a guide. All of the following lines MUST be filled in. If they are
not, you will get an EOF error produced!

   Line 1: This value determines the threshold of informing the user that
           loading is taking place. It is the number of files in the area.
           The slower your system, the smaller this number should be.

       Example: 150

   Line 2: This value determines how often a dot is added to the output
           when there are lots of files in an area.

       Example: 50

   Line 3: Overlay feature. This option will en/disable an output mode which
           causes the new page to be written over the old one instead of
           clearing the screen first. Valid options:

       Example: OVERLAY=ON
       Example: OVERLAY=OFF

   Line 4: This line dis/allows tagging of non-validated files. NOVALID=ON 
           will disallow tagging of non-validated files. Valid options:

       Example: NOVALID=ON
       Example: NOVALID=OFF

   Line 5: This line determines wether or not the user will be bound by their
           current SIG or not. If this is on, then the user will only see
           areas in the SIG they are currently in. Valid options:

       Example: FORCESIG=ON
       Example: FORCESIG=OFF

   Line 6: The command string for LhA file listing. This command handles all
           the lh (-lh0- etc) plus the LhA .RUN files.

       Example: LhA vv 

   Line 7: This is the command that handles listing of ZOO archives.

       Example: ZOO v

   Line 8: This is the command that handles listing of ZIP files.

       Example: UnZip -v

   Line 9: This is the command that handles listing of ARJ files.

       Example: UnArj v

   Line 10: This is the command that handles listing of DMS files.

       Example: DMS View

   Line 11: This is the command that handles ARC files.

       Example: Arc v

   Line 12: This is the external batch editing program. Path and name ONLY!

       Example: DLGConfig:Master/M-BatchFS

   Line 13: This is the parameter list to be passed to the external batch
            editing program. If you are using M-BatchFS, this line should be
            set to M-BatchFS.

       Example: M-BatchFS
       Example: -p%port

   Line 14: This is the external global scanning program.

       Example: DLGConfig:Master/M-Scan

   Line 15: This is the parameter list to be passed to the external global
            file scanner. If you are using M-Scan, this line should be set to
            M-SCAN.

       Example: M-SCAN
       Example: -p%port

   Line 16: This line tells M-TagFS which of the 3 header lines it needs to
            update when a file is un/tagged. Can only be 1, 2, or 3, and
            assumes both variables are on the same line.

       Example: 1

   Line 17: This line is header line 1.

   Line 18: This line is header line 2.

   Line 19: This line is header line 3.

See @{"Custom headers" Link CusHead} for details.

The config file is supplied with the three standard header lines included.

M-TagFS will exit gracefully if it can not find its config file.

@ENDNODE

@NODE CusHead "Using custom headers"

With this version of M-TagFS you can design your own custom headers with a
few restrictions:

  - File area number will ALWAYS pad to 4 characters.
  - Files in area will ALWAYS pad to 4 characters.
  - File area name will ALWAYS pad to 34 characters.
  - Both K and number of files tagged have to be on the same line.

Apart from these restrictions, you can use any of the standard DLG
%-switches. Don't use the file area stats switches as they are not updated
when changing areas.

There are 5 custom %-switches to use in your lines. They are:

  - %AREANUM    - The file area number the user is in.
  - %AREANAME   - The file area name the user is in.
  - %AREAFILES  - The number of files in this area.
  - %BATCHK     - Total KB the user has in their tagged list.
  - %BATCHFILES - Total files the user has in their batch list.

More will be added by request.

When constructing your header lines, simply put the text in, using %-switches
for ANSI color's.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Setting_up "Setting up"

Setting up M-TagFS is very easy.

Create a directory in 'DLGConfig:' called 'Master'.

Unarchive the file into the 'DLGConfig:Master/' directory.

Edit the config file according to the manual.

Add a command to your file menu to call the program:

       DLGConfig:Master/M-TagFS [-A%File_AreaNumber] [-S%File_SigNumber]

If the -A parameter is not given, the user's private area will be used. The
-S option is used for 2 reasons. The first is to pass on to M-Scan. The
second is for the FORCESIG option.

Seasoned users of M-TagFS/M-Tag will notice that the batch/command launch
methods have been removed. This is because there is no need to re-load the
file module in order for the batch commands to see the batch file.

@ENDNODE

@NODE The_help_file "The help file"

The help file is quite simple to change. The format is as following:

topic titleNULL
topic textNULL
topic titleNULL
topic textNULL

Make sure you have an editor that correctly shows these NULL characters.

Each topic title should be one line only, and a maximum of @{b}35 characters@{bu}.
The topic text can contain any characters.  See the included help file for an
example.

There can be a maximum of 40 topics. 

                @{b}ANY MORE THAN 40 AND YOUR AMIGA WILL CRASH!!@{bu}

You can also include DLG %-switches in the topic text @{b}ONLY@{bu}. As always, check
that the switches are being translated correctly.

You can now have multiple versions of the help file available. The format of
the help file name is:

   M-TagFS.HLP.{language}

For example, if you have both French and English users, and you have a
language file for both, you can create both M-TagFS.HLP.English AND
M-TagFS.HLP.French.

To cater for extended language names, only the FIRST word of a language name
is used. For example, a language shown as 'English with IBM ANSI' will use a
help file called 'M-TagFS.HLP.English'

@ENDNODE

@NODE Memory "M-TagFS memory availability"

GFA-Basic allocates a set amount of working RAM when the program is run.
This can cause problems with large file areas.

M-TagFS allows you to test each file area for the amount of free memory
remaining.  To do this, you need to do the following from a shell:

  SetEnv M-Tag.Sysop ""

and then run M-TagFS in your big file areas.

You are told the amount of free memory left (in BYTES).  If this gets low
(less than a 10K), you will have to follow the procedure outlined in
@{"Increasing Internal Memory" link int_mem}.

To turn this feature off, use the following command:

  UnSetEnv M-Tag.Sysop

@ENDNODE

@node int_mem "Increasing Internal Memory"

With this release of M-TagFS, I have added the ability for knowledgable sysops
to increase the working space of GFA. You will need a binary file editer such
as AZap that allows you to edit a binary file.

  - Load the file 'M-TagFS' into the binary editor.
  - Goto the very end of the file.
  - Scan back a page at a time until you see the following text:

              RESERVED: 65536 <--

  - You may change the 65536 to a number in the range of 50000-999999, ie:

              RESERVED: 50000 <-- to RESERVED: 999999<--

    NB: IF REDUCING FROM A 6 DIGIT NUMBER TO A 5 DIGIT NUMBER, ENTER A SPACE
        AS THE 6TH DIGIT!

  - save the changed executable.

The operation is now complete.  Re-test M-TagFS in your big file areas.


@ENDNODE

@node keyfile "Invalid keyfile"

Some sysops may have been lucky enough to download the release of the M-Tag
package released onto AmiNet which had my keyfile in the archive.

If you are such a sysop, be warned that all updates AND any new utilities I
release will NOT function if this invalid keyfile is detected.

@ENDNODE

@NODE History "History"

                      Version History for M-TagFS

Version 0.9  - Initial sysop-only test version.

Version 1.0  - First public release.
             - Fixed lots of logic errors when changing areas.
             - Improved change areas function.
             - Added several new commands.
             - Added a text reading and LhASFX support.
             - Changed header design.
             - Made help files totally sysop configurable.
             - Optimized the code a little.

Version 1.1  - Fixed a problem when showing file info in areas with a number
               of files that causes the last file to be displayed under the
               info panel.
             - Put a screen clear before error output.

Version 1.1a - Fixed a problem with the batch file obtaining a lock under
               certain conditions.
             - Added a small unregistered banner at the end.
             - Changed error output strings a little.

Version 1.2r - Added pack option.
             - Added config file.

Version 1.3r - Added cursor speed.
             - Fixed a bundle of batch list logic bugs.

Version 1.4r - Removed several switches into the config file.
             - Added batch editing.

Version 1.5r - Added private file area support.
             - Added broadcasting of messages.
             - Fixed a small bug in the command options when changing areas.
             - Added configurable archive listers.

Version 1.6r - Fixed a bug in batch edit when list is killed.
             - Fixed a bug that was causing an enforcer hit for eachfile that
               was read in. This was crashing some machines.
             - Fixed a bug in private file area when there were no files.
             - Changed header command line.
             - Added small help notice at run-time.
             - Added text output when boundaries are reached and removed the
               annoying bell.
             - Added some more system message checking.
             - Fixed a problem with the help screen when using slow cursor.
             - Beefed up color correction.
             - Removed M command. Obselete.
             - Moved K command into edit batch function.

Version 1.7r - Now only reads in the area list once. Makes changing areas
               much quicker.
             - Changed error message displayed when a non-listed area was
               chosen.
             - Now auto-pages to next page if pointer at top/bottom of page.
             - Fixed a bug which caused the last valid area scanned to become
               the new area name when RETURN pressed.
             - Fixed a bug which was causing free files not to be tagged as
               free.
             - Changed some wording.
             - Now leaves some messages on the bottom until the line is needed.
             - Now displays '*=New file' after each new screen is sent.
             - Now removes the header lines and uses the full screen when
               changing areas.
             - Now scans archive listing, and if its longer than the users
               screen, it will over-write the title.
             - Added long description support.
             - Added K command.
             - Fixed local mono colors. No longer prints in red.
             - Added search support.
             - Added next/previous area jumping.
             - Fixed a bug which displayed area 0 in header when no files
               existed in an area.
             - Added action strings to 'T:<port>.user'.

Version 1.8r - Added Global search function
             - Added %-switch support in help file
             - Fixed another bug in free file handling.
             - Made the registered version work as a demo version as well!

Version 1.8a - Removed 'r' from name!
             - Beefed up key code detection when arrows are used.
             - Removed the batch editing code. Now uses M-BatchFS.
             - Fixed a problem with sysop access to full program.
             - Removed a few more bell's.

Version 1.8b - Dramatically improved loading speed. Now loads data much
               quicker.
             - Fixed up a 100 byte memory leak when no keyfile present.
             - Added totally configurable external batch editing.

Version 1.9  - Changed program name from M-Tag2 to M-TagFS.
             - Made global file searching truly wildcard capable. Uses the
               full range of AmigaDOS wildcardes.
             - Fixed up a memory leak when using the global file search.
             - Added language extension to help file.

Version 1.95 - Added title changing.
             - Added ! option.
             - Fixed a long-standing bug which showed areas as not existing
               when an upgrade flag is used.

Version 2.0  - Added DLG area CD support.
             - Removed area checking code. Now handled by M-Support.
             - Removed global file searching code. Now uses M-Scan.
             - Changed the way the help file name is read.
             - Added global filepath support.

Version 2.0a - Fixed a bug which caused enforcer hits, and perhaps crashed
               some machines.

Version 2.0b - Fixed a small display error.
             - Added option to tag a non-existant file anyway.

Version 2.0c - Fixed a severe bug when more than 255 files tagged.
             - Fixed even more severe bug when more than 127 files tagged.
               This bug appears to be in DLG itself.
             - Now displays any 'EnterArea.TXT' files found when changing
               areas.
             - Removed 4 enforcer hits on TPTBC
             - Fixed up 2 error messages sent.

Version 2.0d - Added correct 'EnterArea' flag when changing area.
             - Now checks for closed area before allowing user to enter.

Version 2.0e - Added a bit more checking in a few places.

Version 2.0f - Fixed a bug when a new SIG was added to the system
             - Beefed up checking of files and memory before working with
               them.

Version 2.1  - Fixed a problem when viewing archives smaller than 50 bytes.
             - Further beefed up error checking in certain areas.

Version 2.2  - Added configurable headers.
             - Now accepts comma as seperator when inputing file numbers.

Version 3.0  - Fixed a problem with the L command.
             - Removed P option. Hope nobody used it regularly!
             - Made several optimisations.

@ENDNODE

